File: Johannesburg's Charlotte Maxeke hospital. Google Maps JOHANNESBURG - Charlotte Maxeke Academic hospital will reopen on 03 May, according to the Gauteng provincial government.
Patients will be transferred during the weekend of 01 and 02 May. READ: Charlotte Maxeke Hospital reeling after weekend blaze The hospital was shut down last week after a fire damaged some parts of the building. More than 800 patients had to be moved to other facilities. A preliminary report has revealed that the fire affected block 3 and 4 of the hospital. The two blocks will remain closed.